  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The new technology of the motorized Spiral enteroscope, originally developed for deep small&#xD;
      bowel enteroscopy, might potentially overcome some limitations of standard colonoscopy.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Cecal intubation rate represents a key procedural quality parameter in diagnostic&#xD;
      colonoscopy. However, even in experienced hands, a significant percentage of colonoscopies&#xD;
      (1.6-16.7%) remain incomplete because of a failure to intubate the cecum. The new technology&#xD;
      of the motorized Spiral enteroscope, originally developed for deep small bowel enteroscopy,&#xD;
      might potentially overcome some limitations of standard colonoscopy. The study aim was to&#xD;
      evaluate the feasibility and safety of motorized Spiral enteroscopy for difficult&#xD;
      colonoscopies.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
